events.name: Online Event: Cloud Study Jam OnAir with Google
events.description:
Join an early-morning, pre-work code jam online! Learn from experts and access free hands-on labs during this online Cloud Study Jam. In this session, we'll work through a lab in the Google Cloud Run Serverless Workshop. Googlers will be on stand-by to answer your questions about the labs and discuss other serverless technology solutions.

Locally, weʻll have a #cloudjam slack channel open for discussion before, during, and after the event! After the session, keep the learning going. Chat online, finish up the quest, earn a badge, and become eligible for extended access to QwikLabs and other Google Cloud learning tools. If there is enough interest, we will plan future in-person, on-island Cloud Study Jams, supported by Google!

If you can't make the live training but are still interested, sign up anyway! You can still participate with us after the fact, and we'll provide support during the 2 weeks following the event to help everyone complete the quest.

SEPARATE REGISTRATION REQUIRED! To register for this event, please go to: https://cloudonair.withgoogle.com/events/study-jam

Presenters:
Ronan Mandel
Senior Program Manager, Developer Ecosystems
Google Cloud

Kyle Paul
Program Manager
Google Cloud

Local (Slack) Facilitator:
Chryssa Jones
Women Techmakers Ambassador
